#mullet #mullethaircut #melbournefloridahair #melbournefl #melbourneflorida

As you all know, I volunteer rescuing homeless cats in Orlando. The cat on the right is Phillip, a community cat in my neighborhood. Phillip is the FIRST cat I ever TNRed. He is so special to us and our community. I fostered his last litter of kittens, before getting both him and his his soulmate & baby momma, Quack who is on the left in this photo, spayed/neutered. If you are familiar with the iconic feral cats Sad Boy and Lola who are cared for by @poetssquarecats, Phillip and Quack are my community’s Sad Boy & Lola. Phillip is semi friendly and so many of the local neighbors love to visit him and give him treats because he is the most friendly cat in his colony. He has a wonderful caretaker who has “adopted” their colony by feeding them and looking after them. Yesterday Phillip’s caretaker noticed he was suffering from neurological problems. He had a severe head tilt and couldn’t walk or stand. She contacted me for help and after seeing how severe his condition was, I took him to the emergency vet. After doing some bloodwork to get an idea of what might be going on, we discovered he was suffering from severely high levels of sodium which explains all of the symptoms he is experiencing. This condition is testable and has a promising prognosis with IV fluids so we decided to hospitalize Phillip. This was another unexpected very large expense and any support through donations or even just a share would be so appreciated. As a community cat, Phillip looks to us, his community to show him compassion and that includes getting him the vet care he needs. Please consider making a donation to his care if you’re able to ❤️ For full transparency, estimate is included on my story. You can donate through Go Fund Me via the link in my bio, or on the fundraiser with @thewayhomerescue linked here.
